our example, at level 20, your monk should use the Stave of Shielding mainhand. There's no damage bonus at 20, so you put the most damaging weapon there.<br><br>The damage bonus doesn't become a significant portion of your main hand damage until the mid to late 40s.<br><br>For offhand, barring the need for procs, ratio is the only thing that matters in terms of dealing the most damage. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=119554>Sir Kellim</a><BR><a href=http://reviction.lohnetwork.com/>Reviction</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/ufaate.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faate</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>QHills and Clueless</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#628CBC>(8/12/02 1:57:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=198.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   lkvjtlkh</span><hr size=1> Whats been said so farm by shameon and kellim is prety much spot on.<br><br>I did a bit of math for you, until level 56 when your damage bonus becomes 10, Assuming a proc every 120 seconds and 4 minute fights, It will be more damaging to keep your Stave of Shielding in your mainhand and wu's offhand. Duel weild is pretty much purely based on skill check, at 60 you have a 78% chance to have a succesful duel weild check upon the (commonly accepted) average delay between your primary and secondary weapons. In my logging and parsing though, it is easily the most damaging to always go for ratio in mainhand, not delay for general experience groups, only faster ratio for higher mitigation and AC mobs where your damage comes mostly from minimum hits with your damage bonus. <br><br>Now if your talking a low character, then by all means an incredibly fast weapon in offhand will also pump your duel weild skill through the roof and cause much more damage. (try having a 13 warrior with an efreeti standard in offhand, damage is insane because of added duel weilds. Less prevalant as you level and duel weild becomes a thing you can count on for most rounds)<br><br>Small note that is a common misconception. Aggro is NOT only delay based. Hell I hold aggro better with a 40 delay weap than my epic fists, and more consistantly for more damage. <br><br>Most important factor: Do what you think looks cool, not what someone tells you. Just remember to work all your skills on your monk.<br><br>Faate<br>Morell Thules Greatest Lesbian <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=198.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=198.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=198.topic&index=13><img src=http://sevendragons.net/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=198.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.threadControl?topicID=198.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/posticons/techops.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=198.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=198.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification